# Zod v4 Conventions

- Use Zod v4 APIs only.
- Prefer `export const fooSchema = z.object(...)` plus `export type Foo = z.infer<typeof fooSchema>`.
- Keep schema constants in lower camel case and exported inferred types in PascalCase.
- When a schema already defines the transport contract, do not duplicate the shape as a separate handwritten type.

## Validators

- Use v4 validators such as `z.uuid()`, `z.email()`, and `z.iso.datetime()` when those formats are needed.
- Avoid old chained v3-style patterns like `z.string().uuid()` when a v4 top-level validator exists.
